rect.data-tooltip: Phantom Power: 48V for condenser mics. Disable for dynamic mics.
+26dB Pad: Lowers input level for loud sources.
Low Cut: Removes low-frequency rumble.
Gain: Sets input volume. Use PFL to check.
Compression: Smooths out volume peaks.
High EQ: Boost or cut treble frequencies.
Mid EQ: Adjusts midrange for clarity.
Mid Freq: Selects mid EQ frequency.
Low EQ: Boost or cut bass.

FX 1: Controls first effect level.
FX 2: Controls second effect level.
Pan: Sets left/right position in mix.
Channel On: Mute or unmute this channel.
Peak: Warns of signal overload.
Signal: Shows input is active.
Group 1-2: Send to subgroup 1-2.
Group 3-4: Send to subgroup 3-4.
Stereo: Send to main outputs.
PFL: Listen to channel solo.
PFL Active: Solo monitoring on.
Level: Controls channel output.
